e and make it to the Tomb, but were dispatch by the defences there. I would estimate some 200+ giants were killed during this timeframe. The level 60+ giants were known to have dropped items such as Coldain Skin Boots, Swiftbalde of Zek, and similar value items. The faction hits were the same as killing any other giant in EW.<br><br>At some point, we began to be attacked by &quot;traitor&quot; drakes. These were pretty nasty, requiring more effort than the standard zerg used on the giants... needed to allow MT's to gain aggro and put some dedicated healers on them. These drakes gave -CoV, -Yelinak, -Disciples of Kerafyrm. I think prior to this event, Melalefen was the only mob to affect Disciples faction.<br><br>After a couple more hours of continual invasion by giants and traitor drakes, the ENTIRE defensive force repositioned to prepare for a new offensive from the east. I would estimate this defensive line as having 20-30 mobs in formation. Shortly thereafter, a HUGE offensive force of estimated 20-30 mobs formed up to the east (just south of the bridge). There were several 63+ wurms (&quot;molten blight wurm&quot; I think it was), and at least one named 63+ wyvern. Looked to be a VERY nasty war coming. At this point I had to leave and join a guild raid, but over the course of 2-3 more hours, this last wave was repelled (much credit to those who defended against it), and the event ended.<br><br>The GMs awarded a LOT of items to those who were there for the duration of the even. There were even Artifact items and Legendary items handed out (Legendary items are ones that are named after a player, like the Xanthe's Earring of Nature). For example, Rluas (a bard from my guild) was recognized by the GMs for his efforts, and an item (not sure what) was being named after him. Other items given out or dropped by mobs during the final battle: Earring of Living Thunder, Boots of the Storm, Ring of Destruction, FT3 robes, and many other items.<br><br>Tonight we get to visit the &quot;new&quot; sleepers tomb, to see how yesterday's story fits into the scheme of things.<br><br>One last thing... during the event, the zones to GD, IC, and ST were all locked. Once entering EW, the only way out was to get a druid or wizard to port, gate out, or die.<br><br><br>Here are some pictures I managed to take (forgot to get screenshot of final invasion force though <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ):<br><br>Dragon at Sleepers Tomb:<br><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.mindfusioncorp.com/EW_EQ000007.jpg"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br><br><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.mindfusioncorp.com/EW_EQ000009.jpg"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br><br>A team tries to advance towards Kael and intercept a wave of giants:<br><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.mindfusioncorp.com/EW_EQ000010.jpg"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br><br>Just outside the western front, defending against another wave of giants:<br><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.mindfusioncorp.com/EW_EQ000011.jpg"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br><br>Two traitor drakes (Crimson Blood Drake / Ebon Death Drake) manage to make it to the final fortification at ST:<br><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.mindfusioncorp.com/EW_EQ000012.jpg"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br><br>The wurmkind defensive ranks are called into position to defend against the new threat to the east:<br><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.mindfusioncorp.com/EW_EQ000013.jpg"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br> <p><hr width=100%>Easirok Soulsavior<br>Crusader of Stormhammer<br>Subject of Vexare<br><a target="_blank" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=53778">Easirok's Magelo Profile</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udaladmera1.showPubli